I agree with Jon I think - the range of useful values is very very slow to very very fast. 
I think for accessibility it is a clear P1 that it can go slow enough, whatever that is, and I think it is probably an important P2 that it can go fast enough. 
I find, using the speech built into Macintosh, that it is slower than I would like for real efficiency, but it does allow me access to the content (and I am not accustomed to using it yet - I am aware that for an expert user it would be like having a 300 baud telephone line - posssible, but very unpleasant). 
